                            <comment id="468185" author="adilger" created="Wed, 20 Aug 2025 06:06:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Arshad, if you click on the failed subtest number (&lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/search?end_date=2025-08-20&amp;amp;source=sub_tests&amp;amp;start_date=2025-08-14&amp;amp;status=FAIL&amp;amp;sub_test_script_id=d87186e6-5345-11e5-b61c-5254006e85c2&amp;amp;test_set_script_id=7f66aa20-3db2-11e0-80c0-52540025f9af#redirect&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;&lt;tt&gt;test_91&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/a&gt; in this case) it will bring up a search for failures of that subtest in the past week, which only shows one failure.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/search?horizon=2332800&amp;amp;status%5B%5D=FAIL&amp;amp;test_set_script_id=7f66aa20-3db2-11e0-80c0-52540025f9af&amp;amp;sub_test_script_id=d87186e6-5345-11e5-b61c-5254006e85c2&amp;amp;source=sub_tests#redirect&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;Expanding the &lt;tt&gt;Within&lt;/tt&gt; window to 4 weeks&lt;/a&gt; shows that this subtest has failed four times, all of them for patch &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/60689&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/60689&lt;/a&gt; (&quot;&lt;tt&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-8066&quot; title=&quot;Move lustre procfs handling to sysfs and debugfs.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-8066&quot;&gt;LU-8066&lt;/a&gt; mdt: migrate files out of procfs&lt;/tt&gt;&quot;), so this is clearly a regression in that patch (as you have already seen), so no need to open a new Jira ticket in this case.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
